{"word":"φιλόθεος","slug":"φιλόθεος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>φιλόϑεος, ον</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:φίλος\">φίλος</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:θεός\">θεός</a></el>] ‘on intimate terms with God’, <b>fond of God, devoted to God,</b> in wordplay with <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:φιλήδονος\">φιλήδονος</a></el>, of one who has little regard for God’s interests <b><a href='B:620 3:4'>2 Ti 3:4</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Φίλιππος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:Φιλόλογος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}